"   </div>",
"   <div class=\"lgnd\">",
"    Gram stain of stool (x1000) can, in some cases, show Campylobacter jejuni, which are small, faint Gram negative curved rods which may be gull-winged in shape. This finding may provide presumptive evidence of Campylobacter infection prior to the results of stool culture.",
